WER CONTENTS, MAR. 8, 1996
==========================
Subject: WHO Epidemiological Bulletin 8 March 1996
WER and Epidemiological Bulletin E.Mail subscription service

TABLE OF CONTENTS, WER/REH, VOL.71,NO 10, 8 March 1996
Infections due to methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) -
Multicentre epidemiological study in the hospitals of the Pays de la Loire
region, France
Epidemic methicillin-resistant S. aureus, United Kingdom
Surveillance of MRSA, 1983-1995, United Kingdom (Scotland)
Influenza
Cholera in Africa
Cerebrospinal meningitis, Nigeria
Diseases subject to the Regulations

WHO EPIDEMIOLOGICAL BULLETIN SUMMARY FOR PERIOD 4 TO 8 MARCH 1996
CEREBROSPINAL MENINGITIS
NIGERIA:
AS AT 5 MARCH A TOTAL OF 17 668 CASES AND 2550 DEATHS HAVE BEEN REPORTED WITH
MOST CASES OCCURRING IN BAUCHI, JIGAWA, KANO, KADUNA, KATSINA, KEBBI AND SOKOTO
STATES. PRELIMINARY LABORATORY INVESTIGATIONS HAVE IDENTIFIED NEISSERIA
MENINGITIDIS SEROGROUP A IN THREE CASES AND SEROGROUP B IN ONE CASE. VACCINE
AND SUBSTANTIAL QUANTITIES OF ANTIBIOTICS AND INFUSION FLUIDS HAVE BEEN
DISTRIBUTED TO THE AFFECTED STATES TO CONTAIN THE SPREAD OF THE OUTBREAK.
TRAVELLERS TO HYPER-ENDEMIC AREAS WHO MAY BE IN CLOSE CONTACT WITH THE LOCAL
POPULATION SHOULD CONSIDER VACCINATION. VACCINES ARE AVAILABLE AGAINST
SEROGROUP A AND C MENINGOCOCCI WHICH ARE THE MAIN AGENTS OF EPIDEMICS
CHOLERA IN AFRICA
SEVERAL WESTERN AFRICAN COUNTRIES HAVE REPORTED CHOLERA CASES TO WHO IN THE
FIRST TWO MONTHS OF 1996 AND ALTHOUGH SOME HAVE RECORDED RATHER HIGHER FIGURES
THAN AT OTHER TIMES CONTROL MEASURES ARE IN PLACE. THE MEDIA HAVE REPORTED THESE
OUTBREAKS IN VARIOUS WAYS BUT IN ANY CASE THE REPORTS HAVE GIVEN RISE TO A
CERTAIN AMOUNT OF FEAR AMONG TRAVELLERS TO THESE COUNTRIES. WHO WOULD LIKE ONCE
AGAIN TO REMIND TRAVELLERS THAT CHOLERA OUTBREAKS SHOULD NOT PREVENT THEM FROM
VISITING A COUNTRY PROVIDED THAT THE USUAL PRECAUTIONS REGARDING FOOD AND
DRINKING WATER ARE TAKEN.
NIGERIA: AS AT 5 MARCH A TOTAL OF 2836 CASES AND 299 DEATHS HAS BEEN REPORTED.
KANO, KWARA, NIGER, ONDO STATES HAVE REPORTED CASES.
OTHER COUNTRIES REPORTING CHOLERA IN THE PAST WEEK ARE:- CAPE VERDE, NIGER,
SENEGAL, SOMALIA AND MEXICO

